ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: In the past 90 days, on average, how many days per week did you drink alcohol?
In the past 90 days, on average, when you did drink alcohol how many standard drinks would you have in a day?
Notes: A standard drink is defined as one 12 oz can or glass of regular beer, one 5 oz glass of regular wine, or 1.5 oz of regular proof hard liquor or spirits

ElementDescription: In the past 90 days, on one occasion or day, how many times have you had 5 or more standard drinks (for men) or 4 or more standard drinks (for women)
Notes: A standard drink is defined as one 12 oz can or glass of regular beer, one 5 oz glass of regular wine, or 1.5 oz of regular proof hard liquor or spirits

ElementDescription: Standard drinks per week in the past 90 days
